This article is the text of an executive order issued by President Barack Obama on September 10, 2012, regarding the restoration of the Gulf Coast ecosystem. The executive order acknowledges the ecological decline of the Gulf Coast region, particularly due to the Deepwater Horizon Oil Spill in 2010. It highlights the progress made by the Gulf Coast Ecosystem Restoration Task Force in developing a comprehensive restoration plan for the Gulf of Mexico. The executive order terminates the Task Force and establishes the Gulf Restoration Council and the Trustee Council to continue the restoration efforts. It also designates the Environmental Protection Agency (EPA) and the Department of Agriculture (USDA) as additional trustees for natural resource damage assessment and restoration. The executive order emphasizes coordination, cooperation, and accountability among federal entities involved in Gulf Coast restoration. It revokes a previous executive order related to the Task Force.